Hosts. 
<taxonomicName id="51CB25AAFF91BC57FED2FB6BFC26FB2D" authority="(DeGeer, 1774) (Sklyar, 2012)" authorityName="Sklyar" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="DeGeer" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[316,928,1236,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Osmoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriarius">
<emphasis id="A4BF823BFF91BC57FED2FB6BFDB1FB2C" box="[316,567,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Osmoderma coriarius</emphasis>
(DeGeer, 1774) (
<bibRefCitation id="F25A23D8FF91BC57FCECFB6BFC1EFB2D" author="Sklyar, V. Ye." box="[770,920,1236,1263]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" pagination="75 - 90" refId="ref8391" refString="Sklyar, V. Ye. 2012. Four new and two rare species of the family Hypoaspididae (Parasitiformes: Gamasina) from Ukraine. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 20 (1), 75 - 90 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2012">Sklyar, 2012</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96745E29FF91BC57FF35FB4BFDA8F9CD" blockId="2.[166,1225,1204,1615]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">
Remarks. This species was briefly described based on 
<specimenCount id="80CD95A0FF91BC57FC8CFB4BFC64FACD" box="[866,994,1268,1295]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
specimen from 
<taxonomicName id="51CB25AAFF91BC57FB4EFB4AFE00FAEC" authorityName="Sklyar" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="DeGeer" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Osmoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriarius">
<emphasis id="A4BF823BFF91BC57FB4EFB4AFE00FAEC" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Osmoderma coriarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and known only from 
<typeStatus id="4970E08BFF91BC57FD4AFAABFD50FAED" box="[676,726,1300,1327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<collectingRegion id="540F90CBFF91BC57FCA9FAABFB89FAED" box="[839,1039,1300,1327]" country="Ukraine" name="Donets'k" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Donetsk Region</collectingRegion>
). Depository of the 
<typeStatus id="4970E08BFF91BC57FF3AFA8BFE80FA8D" box="[212,262,1332,1359]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">type</typeStatus>
specimen is unknown, microslide with the mite has not been ever deposited (as was indicated in the original description) to the Schmalhausen Institute of Zoology, NAS of 
<collectingCountry id="EEDC1EB9FF91BC57FF29FACBFEACFA4D" box="[199,298,1396,1423]" name="Ukraine" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="540F90CBFF91BC57FED8FACBFEE9FA4D" box="[310,367,1396,1423]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Kyiv</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EEDC1EB9FF91BC57FE92FACBFE5AFA4D" box="[380,476,1396,1423]" name="Ukraine" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(Leonid O. Kolodochka pers. comm.). This nominal species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="51CB25AAFF91BC57FECBFA2AFD31FA6D" authority="Arutunjan, 1990" authorityName="Arutunjan" authorityYear="1990" box="[293,695,1428,1455]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Hypoaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breiti">
<emphasis id="A4BF823BFF91BC57FECBFA2AFE62FA6C" box="[293,484,1428,1454]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Hypoaspis breiti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F25A23D8FF91BC57FE01FA2BFD31FA6D" author="Arutunjan, E. S." box="[495,695,1428,1455]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" pagination="184 - 186" refId="ref5911" refString="Arutunjan, E. S. 1990. New subgenus and new species of the genus Hypoaspis Can., 1884, s. l. (Parasitiformes, Mesostigmata: Laelaptidae). Reports of the Academy of Sciences of Armenia, 91 (4), 184 - 186 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1990">Arutunjan, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, also briefly described based on 
<specimenCount id="80CD95A0FF91BC57FBABFA2BFB4FFA6D" box="[1093,1225,1428,1455]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
from 
<taxonomicName id="51CB25AAFF91BC57FF06FA0BFD08FA0D" authority="(Scopoli, 1763)" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[232,654,1460,1487]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Osmoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eremita">
<emphasis id="A4BF823BFF91BC57FF06FA0BFE50FA0C" box="[232,470,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Osmoderma eremita</emphasis>
(Scopoli, 1763)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="EEDC1EB9FF91BC57FD39FA0BFCA8FA0D" box="[727,814,1460,1487]" name="Austria" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Austria</collectingCountry>
and possibly is its junior synonym (
<bibRefCitation id="F25A23D8FF91BC57FF40FA6BFEF0FA2D" author="Arutunjan, E. S." box="[174,374,1492,1519]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" pagination="184 - 186" refId="ref5911" refString="Arutunjan, E. S. 1990. New subgenus and new species of the genus Hypoaspis Can., 1884, s. l. (Parasitiformes, Mesostigmata: Laelaptidae). Reports of the Academy of Sciences of Armenia, 91 (4), 184 - 186 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1990">Arutunjan, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). We have examined 
<specimenCount id="80CD95A0FF91BC57FD83FA6BFC9FFA2D" box="[621,793,1492,1519]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="51CB25AAFF91BC57FCD3FA6BFBBEFA2C" authorityName="Sklyar" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="DeGeer" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[829,1080,1492,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Osmoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriarius">
<emphasis id="A4BF823BFF91BC57FCD3FA6BFBBEFA2C" box="[829,1080,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Osmoderma coriarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Odesa Region, but no mites were found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96745E29FF91BC57FF35F9ABFC0FF98D" blockId="2.[166,1225,1204,1615]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">
Ukrainian species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="51CB25AAFF91BC57FDADF9AAFD3CF9EC" authorityName="Canestrini, 1884:" authorityYear="1569" box="[579,698,1557,1582]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Hypoaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4BF823BFF91BC57FDADF9AAFD3CF9EC" box="[579,698,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Hypoaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="51CB25AAFF91BC57FBD6F9ABFB4EF9EC" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1914" box="[1080,1224,1556,1582]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Coleolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4BF823BFF91BC57FBD6F9ABFB4EF9EC" box="[1080,1224,1556,1582]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Coleolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry id="EEDC1EB9FF91BC57FF2BF98BFEA3F98D" box="[197,293,1588,1615]" name="Ukraine" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
by the absence lateral incisions on the dorsal shield.
</paragraph>
